ms improved patient care by enhancing the accuracy and accessibility of records and reduced data errors, though challenges such as infrastructure limitations, financial constraints, data privacy concerns, and resistance from healthcare workers persisted as barriers to widespread adoption.Added knowledge: This scoping review underscores the transformative potential of EHR systems in data management and patient care in SSA while identifying key challenges such as infrastructure deficiencies and financial constraints and offering strategic guidance for effective adoption to enhance healthcare outcomes and patient satisfaction.Global health impact for policy and action: This study emphasizes the transformative role of EHR systems in improving healthcare delivery in resource-limited settings like sub-Saharan Africa, highlighting critical areas for policy action—such as infrastructure, funding, data security, training, and strategic interventions—to unlock their potential for enhanced global health outcomes and patient satisfaction. Main findings: This study demonstrates how, between 2014 and 2024, the implementation of EHR systems improved patient care by enhancing the accuracy and accessibility of records and reduced data errors, though challenges such as infrastructure limitations, financial constraints, data privacy concerns, and resistance from healthcare workers persisted as barriers to widespread adoption. Added knowledge: This scoping review underscores the transformative potential of EHR systems in data management and patient care in SSA while identifying key challenges such as infrastructure deficiencies and financial constraints and offering strategic guidance for effective adoption to enhance healthcare outcomes and patient satisfaction. Global health impact for policy and action: This study emphasizes the transformative role of EHR systems in improving healthcare delivery in resource-limited settings like sub-Saharan Africa, highlighting critical areas for policy action—such as infrastructure, funding, data security, training, and strategic interventions—to unlock their potential for enhanced global health outcomes and patient satisfaction.},
