	abstract = {Background: The FAIR principles, under the open science paradigm, aim to improve the Find­ ability, Accessibility, Interoperability and Reusability of digital data. In this sense, the FAIR4­ Health project aimed to apply the FAIR principles in the health research field. For this purpose, a workflow and a set of tools were developed to apply FAIR principles in health research datasets, and validated through the demonstration of the potential impact that this strategy has on health research management outcomes.
Objective: This paper aims to describe the analysis of the impact on health research management outcomes of the FAIR4Health solution.
